skyevault-ops/
│── backend/
│   ├── security_monitoring/  # Blue Team (Defensive Security)
│   │   ├── iam_checker.py      # Checks IAM roles, MFA, privilege escalation risks
│   │   ├── cloudtrail_checker.py # Ensures logging & GuardDuty are enabled
│   │   ├── s3_auditor.py       # Detects public S3 buckets & misconfigurations
│   │   ├── ec2_security.py     # Checks security groups, open ports, vulnerabilities
│   │   ├── logging.py          # Handles security alerts & event tracking
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │
│   ├── penetration_testing/  # Red Team (Offensive Security)
│   │   ├── recon.py           # Finds AWS resources, open services
│   │   ├── network_scan.py    # Runs nmap on EC2 instances
│   │   ├── s3_exploit.py      # Attempts public bucket write/read
│   │   ├── privilege_escalation.py # Checks for IAM misconfigurations & lateral movement
│   │   ├── attack_simulation.py # Simulates real-world AWS attacks
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │
│   ├── reporting/  # Logging & Data Analysis
│   │   ├── generate_reports.py  # Creates security & pentest reports
│   │   ├── s3_storage.py        # Saves logs to an S3 bucket
│   │   ├── sns_alerts.py        # Sends notifications via AWS SNS
│   │   ├── __init__.py
│   │
│   ├── config.py  # Configuration settings (AWS credentials, logging settings)
│   ├── utils.py   # Shared helper functions
│   ├── main.py    # Main execution script, toggles between Pentest Mode & Security Mode
│
│── frontend/ (To be built later)
│── docs/ (Documentation for how to use SkyeVault Ops)
│── README.md  (Project overview & setup instructions)
│── requirements.txt  (Python dependencies)
│── .gitignore